gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 134, Warriors 133
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings defeated the Warriors, 134-133. Harrison Barnes led the way for the Kings with a career-high 39 points (14-24 FG, 7-12 3PT FG), along with four rebounds and two steals, while Domantas Sabonis added 18 points, eight rebounds and 13 assists in the victory. Stephen Curry (33 points, six rebounds, six 3PM) and Jonathan Kuminga (career-high 31 points) combined for 64 points for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Kings improve to 25-18 on the season, while the Warriors fall to 19-23.
